Class NbtCompound

  • NbtTag
    • br.com.gamemods.nbtmanipulator.NbtCompound

  • public class NbtCompound
extends NbtTag

    A key-value mapping tag similar to MutableMap.

    It's the main heart of NBT files and usually contains complex structures.

    • Constructor Detail

      • NbtCompound

        public NbtCompound(@NotNull
                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,br.com.gamemods.nbtmanipulator.NbtTag> value)

        A key-value mapping tag similar to MutableMap.

        It's the main heart of NBT files and usually contains complex structures.

        Parameters:
        value -

        The wrapped MutableMap which contains all key-value mappings. The map instance will be linked so any modification will also change the tag mappings.

        All get functions which are not prefixed with Nullable and NbtCompound.get will throw a ClassCastException if the tag is mapped to a different class then the method used. For example if a given compound have a example=NbtInt(2) and you try to read it using NbtCompound.getShort, an exception will be thrown.

        All get functions which are not prefixed with Nullable and NbtCompound.get will throw TypeCastException if no value is mapped to the given name. This will change in future.

        See Also:
        MutableMap

      • NbtCompound

        public NbtCompound()

        Creates an empty compound.

      • NbtCompound

        public NbtCompound(@NotNull
                   kotlin.Pair... tags)

        Creates a compound which maps the Pair.first value to the Pair.second tag initially.

        The given tags will be linked, so modifications to them will also affects the compound value.

        See Also:
        Pair.first, Pair.second

      • copyFrom

        public void copyFrom(@NotNull
                     NbtCompound other,
                     @NotNull
                     java.lang.String tagName,
                     @Nullable
                     NbtTag p)

        Checks if the other compound have a given tag, if it has then place it in this compound.

        The tag will be linked, so any change in the tag will also affect both compounds.

        Parameters:
        other - The compound that will be checked
        tagName - The name of the tag that will be mapped
        p - If the other compound doesn't have the tag then this parameter will be used.

      • copyTo

      • getValue

        @NotNull
public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,br.com.gamemods.nbtmanipulator.NbtTag> getValue()

        The wrapped MutableMap which contains all key-value mappings. The map instance will be linked so any modification will also change the tag mappings.

        All get functions which are not prefixed with Nullable and NbtCompound.get will throw a ClassCastException if the tag is mapped to a different class then the method used. For example if a given compound have a example=NbtInt(2) and you try to read it using NbtCompound.getShort, an exception will be thrown.

        All get functions which are not prefixed with Nullable and NbtCompound.get will throw TypeCastException if no value is mapped to the given name. This will change in future.

        See Also:
        MutableMap, NbtCompound.get, ClassCastException, NbtCompound.getShort, NbtCompound.get, TypeCastException
